Tutorial example 1
==================

This is the example of the tutorial's "Fist Component" chapter.
It is thought as an entry to the component based development using CCM Tools.


How to build and run:
---------------------

a) CarRental component, mirror component and test client

# Generate idl3 and idl3 mirror files in the right structure
$ ccmtools-generate idl3 -o CarRental/idl3 *.idl
$ ccmtools-generate idl3mirror -o CarRental/idl3 *.idl

# Generate component and mirror component logic as well as a test client
$ ccmtools-generate c++local -o CarRental -ICarRental/idl3/interface CarRental/idl3/interface/BigBusiness/*.idl
$ ccmtools-generate c++local -a -o CarRental -ICarRental/idl3/component -ICarRental/idl3/interface CarRental/idl3/component/BigBusiness/*.idl
$ ccmtools-generate c++local-test -o CarRental -ICarRental/idl3/component -ICarRental/idl3/interface CarRental/idl3/component/BigBusiness/CarRental.idl

# Copy business logic and test cases into the component directory
$ cp impl/* CarRental/impl/

# Compile the components and run the unit test
$ confix.py --bootstrap --configure --packageroot=`pwd`/CarRental --make --targets=check


b) A client application

# Install the components
$ confix.py --packageroot=`pwd`/CarRental --make --targets=install

# Compile and run the client
$ confix.py --bootstrap --configure --packageroot=`pwd`/CarRentalClient --make --targets=install
$ CCM_INSTALL/bin/CarRentalClient_src_client

# Uninstall client and components
$ confix.py --packageroot=`pwd`/CarRentalClient --make --targets=uninstall
$ confix.py --packageroot=`pwd`/CarRental --make --targets=uninstall